In a speech at the Rose Garden, President Biden thanked Vice President Kamala Harris, House Speaker Nancy Pelosi, Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer, and other members of Congress for their work in passing the American Rescue Plan. He highlighted the key provisions of the plan, including direct payments of $1,400 for individuals and families, extended unemployment benefits, funding for schools, small businesses, and healthcare, and support for food and nutrition programs. The President emphasized the importance of this legislation in addressing the urgent needs of the American people and rebuilding the economy from the bottom up. He also acknowledged the challenges in implementing the plan effectively and called for careful oversight to prevent waste and fraud. President Biden expressed his commitment to continue working for the American people and delivering on his promises.